FACTORIAL USING FUNCTION

AIM:
Write a PL/SQL program to find factorial of a number using function.

ALGORITHM:
Step1: Start
Step2: Accept an integer input num
Step3: Declare variables fact=1
Step4: Iterate from 1 to num
4.1: fact=fact*i
Step5: Return fact
Step6: Stop


CODE

CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION FACTORIAL(NUM INTEGER)
RETURN INTEGER IS

FACT INTEGER:=1;

BEGIN

FOR I IN 1..NUM LOOP
FACT:=FACT*I;
END LOOP;
RETURN FACT;
END;
/

DECLARE
NUM INTEGER;
RESULT INTEGER;
BEGIN
NUM:=6;
RESULT:=FACTORIAL(NUM);
DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('Factorial is:'||RESULT);
END;
/
